# ðŸ”¶ 1. Theory: Date Object
> The Date object lets you work with dates and times.

### âœ… Create a Date object:
```js
let now = new Date();
console.log(now);
```

### âœ… Common Methods of Date Object:
- Method            | Description
- getFullYear()	    | Gets the year (e.g. 2025)
- getMonth()	    | Gets the month (0 = Jan, 11 = Dec)
- getDate()	        | Gets the day of the month
- getDay()	        | Gets the weekday (0 = Sunday, 6 = Saturday)
- getHours()	    | Gets the hour
- getMinutes()	    | Gets the minutes
- getSeconds()	    | Gets the seconds
- toLocaleString()	| Converts date to a readable format

#### ðŸ”§ Example:
```js
let now = new Date();
console.log("Year:", now.getFullYear());
console.log("Month:", now.getMonth() + 1); // +1 because it's 0-based
console.log("Date:", now.getDate());
console.log("Hour:", now.getHours());
console.log("Minutes:", now.getMinutes());
```